author: arkurth
msg: xCAT.pm's image_size() sub was returning undefined if the image didn't exist, causing errors if an attempt was made to use the undefined value. I changed this sub to return 0 if the image doesn't exist, and undefined only if a problem occurred trying to get the image size.
Modified capture_monitor() in xCAT21.pm and xCAT.pm to check if result from get_image_size() is defined.
